rooms.Name: A room in the dungeons
rooms.Description:
You are in the dungeons of Diablo.  The floor is made of solid, smooth stone,
riddled with cracks, though that is hard to tell since it is covered in dirt
and rubble.  Rags, bones, and dust collect in piles.  Occasionally a rat
scurries from one dark corner to another.  You can hear the scuffling of feet
over the stone floor in the distance, far too heavy for anything as small as
a rat.  Moans, growls and other strange sounds resonate throughout this
place, echoing off the stone floors and walls.  Shadows flicker in the
torchlight, making movement where there is none, and obscuring your sight.

rooms.Name: A cell in the dungeons
rooms.Description:
You are now behind the bars of the cell.  A couple skeletons sit on the
floor, remnants of past occupants.  The bars are rusty and look like they
will fall apart, yet they hold sturdy in their places.  The ground is covered
in the clothes of men long dead, and those not quite dead enough.  A movement
in the corner catches your eye.  Was it just a rat scurrying through the
shadows, or did that skeleton's arm just move?

rooms.Name: A small library in the dungeons
rooms.Description:
You have entered a room which has been sealed off for centuries.  Bookshelves
line the walls, filled with musty old tomes.  Dust covers everything like a
thick wool blanket.  Several podiums are set up around the room, each with an
open tome on them.  These look like the only books left that are in any kind
of condition to be read.  The ones on the shelves crumble to dust when you
try to pick them up.  The floor is covered in what was once a thick,
expensive carpet, though now it is riddled with holes and rotted away from
the dampness.

There are doors to the north and south.

rooms.Name: The beginning of the dungeons
rooms.Description:
You have just entered the dungeons of Diablo.  The dungeon spreads out before
you, dark and mysterious.  The floor under your feet is covered in filth.
Dirt, dust, and other sludge sticks to your boots.  Under all the dirt, the
floor is made of cracked stone, like the walls and the ceiling.  Your lantern
throws flickering shadows on the walls.  You can sense many evil things
lurking down here.  Ready your weapons, adventurer, danger lies ahead, and
it's looking for you.

over the stone floor in the distance, far too heavy for anything as small as
a rat.  Moans, growls and other strange sounds resonate throughout this
place, echoing off the stone floors and walls.  Shadows flicker in the
torchlight, making movement where there is none, and obscuring your sight.

There are doors to the east and west.
